full_text: I'mma need people (e.g., blog posts) to stop referring to remote learning as online learning. These two things, conceptually & practically, are not the same. They share some challenges and best practices, but most students aren't shifting to online, they're shifting to remote.

full_text: I hope I never forget how this feels. And I hope all the grad students I know get to have this same experience. This is the joy in academia, in grad school. This is the way it should be for everyone. 24/end
full_text(utf-8): b'I hope I never forget how this feels. And I hope all the grad students I know get to have this same experience. This is the joy in academia, in grad school. This is the way it should be for everyone. 24/end'

full_text: I'm instead going to spend quite a bit of time just living in this moment, stretching it out, milking it for all its worth. Because in honesty, it's not just a couple hours or one day - it's the last 10-13 years building toward this. 23/
full_text(utf-8): b"I'm instead going to spend quite a bit of time just living in this moment, stretching it out, milking it for all its worth. Because in honesty, it's not just a couple hours or one day - it's the last 10-13 years building toward this. 23/"

full_text: Other friends rotated in and out, masks on, sanitizer in hand. Just love on love on love. I can't remember having felt this way since the day I got married. So for now, I'm not going to think of all the change that's about to happen. 22/
full_text(utf-8): b"Other friends rotated in and out, masks on, sanitizer in hand. Just love on love on love. I can't remember having felt this way since the day I got married. So for now, I'm not going to think of all the change that's about to happen. 22/"

full_text: My delightful friend Amber had arranged a car parade of grad students. She blared pomp and circumstance and dropped off an incredibly thoughtful gift box. I cried and my heart was so full. 21/
full_text(utf-8): b'My delightful friend Amber had arranged a car parade of grad students. She blared pomp and circumstance and dropped off an incredibly thoughtful gift box. I cried and my heart was so full. 21/'

full_text: My mom had sent a bottle and my best friend from high school had sent a bottle. We ate cookies and drank champagne.  I put on a feather boa. and then... 20/
full_text(utf-8): b'My mom had sent a bottle and my best friend from high school had sent a bottle. We ate cookies and drank champagne.  I put on a feather boa. and then... 20/'

full_text: My neighbor put balloons and a congrats sign into my yard. The whole group of neighbors was gathered in my driveway and the adjacent driveway. My husband had baked my fave cookies and popped my fave bottle of champagne...19/
full_text(utf-8): b'My neighbor put balloons and a congrats sign into my yard. The whole group of neighbors was gathered in my driveway and the adjacent driveway. My husband had baked my fave cookies and popped my fave bottle of champagne...19/'

full_text: Of course, it's 2020, so there was no get-together with my committee. This made me sad and still makes me sad. But my friends and neighbors did the most incredible job of making me feel loved 18/
full_text(utf-8): b"Of course, it's 2020, so there was no get-together with my committee. This made me sad and still makes me sad. But my friends and neighbors did the most incredible job of making me feel loved 18/"

full_text: When I was welcomed back to the zoom, it was as "Dr. Soicher" for the very first time. And I didn't feel relieved, I hadn't been worried that I wouldn't pass, but I felt thrilled. It was truly a day that I never thought I'd see (if you'dve asked 10-15 years ago) 17/
full_text(utf-8): b'When I was welcomed back to the zoom, it was as "Dr. Soicher" for the very first time. And I didn\'t feel relieved, I hadn\'t been worried that I wouldn\'t pass, but I felt thrilled. It was truly a day that I never thought I\'d see (if you\'dve asked 10-15 years ago) 17/'

full_text: Then I had to go, while they "discussed the outcome". I video chatted my folks. My dad raved about how he "understood everything I said"! He was so proud of himself, and of me for explaining it so well. 16/
full_text(utf-8): b'Then I had to go, while they "discussed the outcome". I video chatted my folks. My dad raved about how he "understood everything I said"! He was so proud of himself, and of me for explaining it so well. 16/'

full_text: I was able to finally really engage with other scientists about my science and I'm so grateful that it was professional, collegial, even warm-hearted. That's how I felt the whole time. Like everything was just coming neatly together. 15/
full_text(utf-8): b"I was able to finally really engage with other scientists about my science and I'm so grateful that it was professional, collegial, even warm-hearted. That's how I felt the whole time. Like everything was just coming neatly together. 15/"

full_text: Next up - questions from my committee. And honestly, though I had been dreading that part the most, it was incredible. It was just like a warm fire-side chat with colleagues (even friends). 14/
full_text(utf-8): b'Next up - questions from my committee. And honestly, though I had been dreading that part the most, it was incredible. It was just like a warm fire-side chat with colleagues (even friends). 14/'

full_text: As predicted, a handful of them didn't understand that they had to leave. And I painfully hit the "remove" button on Zoom, thinking I'd explain later about why they had to get the boot. 13/
full_text(utf-8): b'As predicted, a handful of them didn\'t understand that they had to leave. And I painfully hit the "remove" button on Zoom, thinking I\'d explain later about why they had to get the boot. 13/'

full_text: Then, the time came for them all to leave. They left kind messages in the chat. They called out how much they loved me - furtively, as though someone might scold them. It was cute. Very cute. 12/
full_text(utf-8): b'Then, the time came for them all to leave. They left kind messages in the chat. They called out how much they loved me - furtively, as though someone might scold them. It was cute. Very cute. 12/'

full_text: I couldn't wait to answer every single one. While I did, I paged through *multiple* screens of faces - colleagues, parents, grandparents, friends - in wonder that so many people would be there for me. I reflected on all the ways they had always been there for me. 11/
full_text(utf-8): b"I couldn't wait to answer every single one. While I did, I paged through *multiple* screens of faces - colleagues, parents, grandparents, friends - in wonder that so many people would be there for me. I reflected on all the ways they had always been there for me. 11/"

full_text: And, as usually happens for me, I sort of "blacked out" during my presentation. It felt so fast, it all went by in a blur, and then the questions rolled in 10/
full_text(utf-8): b'And, as usually happens for me, I sort of "blacked out" during my presentation. It felt so fast, it all went by in a blur, and then the questions rolled in 10/'

full_text: It was a chance to let everyone get to know me a little bit better. To understand my priorities. To see that every day I work hard to bring about change in my own small way. To know more about my investment in myself, my students, my dept., my uni. 9/
full_text(utf-8): b'It was a chance to let everyone get to know me a little bit better. To understand my priorities. To see that every day I work hard to bring about change in my own small way. To know more about my investment in myself, my students, my dept., my uni. 9/'

full_text: An opp to explain why I live thousands of miles away from my family. Why I only come home to visit at Christmas. What it means to "still be in school." The end product of "why I work all the time and am always tired." 8/
full_text(utf-8): b'An opp to explain why I live thousands of miles away from my family. Why I only come home to visit at Christmas. What it means to "still be in school." The end product of "why I work all the time and am always tired." 8/'

full_text: I opened with "I'm excited to share my research with you today" - and nothing has ever been more true. I was ready and really looking forward to telling all these people what I had been doing for the last four years. 7/
full_text(utf-8): b'I opened with "I\'m excited to share my research with you today" - and nothing has ever been more true. I was ready and really looking forward to telling all these people what I had been doing for the last four years. 7/'

full_text: I almost sobbed uncontrollably. And I wasn't ashamed of it. I let everyone know - I'm #FirstGen college student and this show of support is just incredibly overwhelming. Then, I got down to business. 6/
full_text(utf-8): b"I almost sobbed uncontrollably. And I wasn't ashamed of it. I let everyone know - I'm #FirstGen college student and this show of support is just incredibly overwhelming. Then, I got down to business. 6/"

full_text: B/c my defense was on Zoom, I invited every friend and family member I thought would want to watch me chatter away for 40 minutes. At the start of my defense, roughly 60 of my friends/family were logged on. I cried. 5/
full_text(utf-8): b'B/c my defense was on Zoom, I invited every friend and family member I thought would want to watch me chatter away for 40 minutes. At the start of my defense, roughly 60 of my friends/family were logged on. I cried. 5/'

full_text: By Monday (two days out), I was a complete and utter mess. Luckily, I had also scheduled an appt with my therapist. After that session, I felt spent but also reinvigorated. I started to look forward to my defense. On Tuesday, my last practice felt amazing. 4/
full_text(utf-8): b'By Monday (two days out), I was a complete and utter mess. Luckily, I had also scheduled an appt with my therapist. After that session, I felt spent but also reinvigorated. I started to look forward to my defense. On Tuesday, my last practice felt amazing. 4/'

full_text: About a week out, I couldn't concentrate on anything, including mustering up the energy to work on my slides or practice my talk. Luckily, I had some scheduled with my advisor that were more or less hard deadlines 3/
full_text(utf-8): b"About a week out, I couldn't concentrate on anything, including mustering up the energy to work on my slides or practice my talk. Luckily, I had some scheduled with my advisor that were more or less hard deadlines 3/"

full_text: Although the defense feels acute, I've been learning and studying in the area of my defense for the past two years (+/-). I love my research and I honestly think it is an important & unique contribution to the literature 2/
full_text(utf-8): b"Although the defense feels acute, I've been learning and studying in the area of my defense for the past two years (+/-). I love my research and I honestly think it is an important & unique contribution to the literature 2/"

full_text: @CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 When people characterize themselves as one type of learner, it more or less pigeon-holes them and restricts them. Similar to "being a math person" or "being a science person". Although these things may come easier to some people, no one is UNABLE to learn them. 5/5
full_text(utf-8): b'@CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 When people characterize themselves as one type of learner, it more or less pigeon-holes them and restricts them. Similar to "being a math person" or "being a science person". Although these things may come easier to some people, no one is UNABLE to learn them. 5/5'

full_text: @CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 Certainly more beneficial to put our efforts where they can make the biggest difference: generalizable knowledge about learning - e.g., retrieval practice benefits everyone, spaced practice better for long-term retention. 4/
full_text(utf-8): b'@CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 Certainly more beneficial to put our efforts where they can make the biggest difference: generalizable knowledge about learning - e.g., retrieval practice benefits everyone, spaced practice better for long-term retention. 4/'

full_text: @CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 Rather, most people learn through repetition (need more than one presentation) and it is helpful to consider information in multiple ways (whether this is in "modalities" like visual/auditory or some other characteriziation). 3/
full_text(utf-8): b'@CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 Rather, most people learn through repetition (need more than one presentation) and it is helpful to consider information in multiple ways (whether this is in "modalities" like visual/auditory or some other characteriziation). 3/'

full_text: @CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 The problem is when people think they "can't learn" because instructions isn't matched to their learning. This promotes a more or less rigid view of learning. "I can't learn math because I'm an auditory learner, writing it out isn't helpful". 2/
full_text(utf-8): b'@CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 The problem is when people think they "can\'t learn" because instructions isn\'t matched to their learning. This promotes a more or less rigid view of learning. "I can\'t learn math because I\'m an auditory learner, writing it out isn\'t helpful". 2/'

full_text: @CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 The main idea is that there doesn't appear to be a benefit for matching instruction to a person's "learning style". Instead, it depends on the info being learned (e.g., procedural learning best through movement, graphs best through visual presentation)...1/
full_text(utf-8): b'@CogSciGirlPhD @CasualUser5 @rogers_k8 The main idea is that there doesn\'t appear to be a benefit for matching instruction to a person\'s "learning style". Instead, it depends on the info being learned (e.g., procedural learning best through movement, graphs best through visual presentation)...1/'

full_text: @OnlineCrsLady @academicswrite So, I'm terrible at/hate editing, but LOVE revisions. The first requires me to see something I (probably) can't. The second requires critical thinking to figure out how to address a need. That second thing is a fun adventure.

full_text: @OnlineCrsLady @academicswrite When someone says "editing" - I think of going back through something I've written and trying to spot where it can be improved, what's missing + copyediting, etc. "Revisions" means that someone else has read/provided feedback on my work and it's my job to recreate based on that.

full_text: It would free up space for instructors to reach out to their students, to support them intellectually and emotionally. That can't happen well when instructors are stressed beyond reason about how to even approach the problem in the first place.

full_text: Plus, thinking of all the time and cognitive effort that could have been saved if so many of these folks already had online teaching skills in their arsenal. I KNOW #RemoteTeaching is NOT the same as online, but the transition is easier for folks w/ online exp.

full_text: Let me be clear I'm not chastising anyone. I'm saying that trying to figure out effective online pedagogy gets you thinking like nothing else can and creates a fundamental shift in how you approach teaching and ALL teachers would benefit from this experience. #HigherEd

Building a relationship with your dog will go so far in improving her behavior across all other situations. It's not easy but it's rewarding. 4/4"

full_text: @cwalterswrite I chimed in because our dog didn't have any anxiety as a pup, but developed a lot of anxiety as a juvenile and is now on meds and has been in private training for reactivity for about 2 years now. I "give in" where I need to if it is helpful to her and to me. 3/
full_text(utf-8): b'@cwalterswrite I chimed in because our dog didn\'t have any anxiety as a pup, but developed a lot of anxiety as a juvenile and is now on meds and has been in private training for reactivity for about 2 years now. I "give in" where I need to if it is helpful to her and to me. 3/'

full_text: @cwalterswrite Of course, following "best practices" in training is ideal, but also your dog's needs might just be different. Also, your needs might be different. We also now leave our pup out of her crate when we leave the house (pre-COVID). She is mostly good. 2/
full_text(utf-8): b'@cwalterswrite Of course, following "best practices" in training is ideal, but also your dog\'s needs might just be different. Also, your needs might be different. We also now leave our pup out of her crate when we leave the house (pre-COVID). She is mostly good. 2/'

full_text: @cwalterswrite This is so hard. Crate training is an excellent go-to. But our dog really struggled and we let her sleep out of her crate (with her doggie sister) and she is fine. No chewing. Occasional potty accidents (but I think that would happen regardless). 1/

full_text: @MoraReinka They don't have to make the changes, but if they don't, they have to provide an explanation of why not. This brings intention to their writing/revising process. I'm just an N of 1, but this process reduced my own time grading and resulted in better writing from my students 8/8
full_text(utf-8): b"@MoraReinka They don't have to make the changes, but if they don't, they have to provide an explanation of why not. This brings intention to their writing/revising process. I'm just an N of 1, but this process reduced my own time grading and resulted in better writing from my students 8/8"

full_text: @MoraReinka When students revise their drafts, they must write a letter to the editor (me) about how they have addressed each of the changes suggested by their reviewer (change 4(?), I lost count, hahaha). This is part of their grade, so they can't ignore the feedback. 7/
full_text(utf-8): b"@MoraReinka When students revise their drafts, they must write a letter to the editor (me) about how they have addressed each of the changes suggested by their reviewer (change 4(?), I lost count, hahaha). This is part of their grade, so they can't ignore the feedback. 7/"

full_text: @MoraReinka Plus, students who didn't do such a great job have the opportunity to see papers from students who have done the intro well. The peer review is very specific, so students received structured, helpful feedback. 6/
full_text(utf-8): b"@MoraReinka Plus, students who didn't do such a great job have the opportunity to see papers from students who have done the intro well. The peer review is very specific, so students received structured, helpful feedback. 6/"

full_text: @MoraReinka The students write drafts of their intro and peer review it in class (change 2) using a rubric that helps highlight the structure of an introduction (change 3). Because the students are all writing on the same topic, they're actually able to provide useful feedback 5/
full_text(utf-8): b"@MoraReinka The students write drafts of their intro and peer review it in class (change 2) using a rubric that helps highlight the structure of an introduction (change 3). Because the students are all writing on the same topic, they're actually able to provide useful feedback 5/"

full_text: @MoraReinka Do they still write a paper? Yes, a registered report in fact (change 1). All students research/write on the same topic. This helps me be on top of the relevant literature and decreases the amount of time I spend trying to figure out what they have/n't done. 4/
full_text(utf-8): b"@MoraReinka Do they still write a paper? Yes, a registered report in fact (change 1). All students research/write on the same topic. This helps me be on top of the relevant literature and decreases the amount of time I spend trying to figure out what they have/n't done. 4/"

full_text: @MoraReinka Will the majority of my students continue to grad school? No. Is a full APA-style paper the best use of their time or my time? Probably not. My answers to these questions have led to some changes for me in my teaching. 3/
full_text(utf-8): b'@MoraReinka Will the majority of my students continue to grad school? No. Is a full APA-style paper the best use of their time or my time? Probably not. My answers to these questions have led to some changes for me in my teaching. 3/'

full_text: @MoraReinka Scientific writing is its own genre, in need of its own class, I would argue. And then, there's more to consider about who our students are. 2/
full_text(utf-8): b"@MoraReinka Scientific writing is its own genre, in need of its own class, I would argue. And then, there's more to consider about who our students are. 2/"

full_text: @MoraReinka I guess it depends on the learning outcomes for your class, but going back to grad school really gave me some perspective. Did I know how to write well scientifically in undergrad? No. In fact, I feel like I have had to write a ton and read oodles of books, still not an expert 1/
